WEBVTT

00:02.380 --> 00:06.040
Dre: Marriage --
the sign of eternal love

00:06.040 --> 00:10.040
and, yet, in the U.S.,
every 38 seconds...
[ Screaming ]

00:10.040 --> 00:12.120
...someone gets divorced.

00:12.120 --> 00:15.080
That equates
to 94 divorces per hour...

00:28.960 --> 00:31.920
It makes me wonder --
why do I even bother

00:31.920 --> 00:34.500
wasting money
on wedding presents?

00:34.500 --> 00:37.080
But it's not just about
the couples who get hurt.

00:37.080 --> 00:38.830
It's the families.

00:38.830 --> 00:42.120
The collateral damage
in any divorce is the kids

00:42.120 --> 00:44.420
because they didn't ask
for any of this.

00:46.210 --> 00:48.170
All right, let me be clear.
Mm-hmm.

00:48.170 --> 00:50.500
Your mother and I
are not getting a divorce.

00:50.500 --> 00:53.080
Mnh-mnh.
We're just taking
some space.

00:53.080 --> 00:54.670
We're just taking
some space.
Mm-hmm.

00:54.670 --> 00:56.880
Totally temporary,
totally cool,

00:56.880 --> 00:58.500
and just nothing
to worry about.

00:58.500 --> 01:00.170
Nothing to worry about.
Mnh-mnh.

01:00.170 --> 01:01.580
There's no need
to tell your friends.
Mnh-mnh.

01:01.580 --> 01:04.120
Or your teachers because
they don't need to know.

01:04.120 --> 01:05.210
'Cause it's
totally temporary.

01:05.210 --> 01:06.960
Totally temporary.

01:06.960 --> 01:08.540
Yeah,
and nothing to worry about.

01:08.540 --> 01:10.620
Nothing to worry about.

01:10.620 --> 01:11.830
Yeah.

01:11.830 --> 01:12.920
Any questions?

01:12.920 --> 01:14.960
-Yeah.
-Okay. Great.

01:14.960 --> 01:16.120
Okay, yep.
Nope, nope.

01:21.250 --> 01:24.210
So, what does "space" mean?

01:24.210 --> 01:26.120
Yeah, because when I
think of space,

01:26.120 --> 01:28.880
I think of a vacuous,
freezing-cold environment

01:28.880 --> 01:30.620
incapable
of sustaining life.

01:30.620 --> 01:33.000
Or...
Oh. Or.

01:33.000 --> 01:36.460
...it is a separate,
warm...

01:36.460 --> 01:38.670
-Mm-hmm.
-...healthy environment...

01:38.670 --> 01:41.120
Yes.
...where we can process
our feelings

01:41.120 --> 01:43.170
and then
come back together...

01:43.170 --> 01:44.380
-Stronger.
-Stronger. Mm-hmm.

01:44.380 --> 01:46.120
Okay.
So who's moving out?

01:46.120 --> 01:47.330
-What?
-Hm?

01:47.330 --> 01:49.580
Somebody is moving out.
I've seen this on TV.

01:49.580 --> 01:51.210
Okay.

01:51.210 --> 01:52.880
There's gonna be a coatrack
in somebody's car.

01:52.880 --> 01:54.120
-No, sweetie.
-No, no.

01:54.120 --> 01:55.460
-Mm-hmm.
-No.

01:55.460 --> 01:56.880
But -- But I don't
want to move out.

01:56.880 --> 01:58.790
I just memorized
our address.

01:58.790 --> 02:01.250
Okay, no one is moving out,
all right?

02:01.250 --> 02:02.920
Mnh-mnh.

02:02.920 --> 02:06.580
We are trying this new thing
called "nesting"...

02:06.580 --> 02:09.000
Nesting.
...where we share
an apartment...

02:09.000 --> 02:11.380
-So cool.
-...and take turns living here.

02:11.380 --> 02:13.960
That way, you guys don't have
to go back and forth.

02:13.960 --> 02:16.000
Spoken like a guy
with the coatrack.

02:16.000 --> 02:17.790
I know it's a lot,
but we're gonna be here

02:17.790 --> 02:19.000
talking you
through all of it.

02:19.000 --> 02:20.290
-Yeah.
-Right here with you.

02:20.290 --> 02:23.040
-All of it.
-So Dad's gonna get Mondays.

02:23.040 --> 02:24.420
No, no.
I get Tuesday.

02:24.420 --> 02:26.620
Junior: The more Mom and Dad
kept talking,

02:26.620 --> 02:30.040
the more questions we had,
so we all did "a Jack"

02:30.040 --> 02:32.080
and just nodded
and smiled like we knew

02:32.080 --> 02:33.250
what they were talking about.

02:33.250 --> 02:35.580
But the dog and Ruby
stay here at all times.

02:35.580 --> 02:37.040
-Oh.
-They'll be here.

02:37.040 --> 02:38.210
-Yeah.
-Ruby stays here.

02:40.120 --> 02:41.960
Uh,
so, what just happened?

02:41.960 --> 02:43.830
Mom and Dad are over,
dummy.

02:43.830 --> 02:46.290
We're lucky if this doesn't end
in Dad kidnapping four of us.

02:46.290 --> 02:47.460
There's five of us.

02:47.460 --> 02:48.790
Sorry, Junior.

02:48.790 --> 02:51.330
Well, she's not wrong.
They got an apartment.

02:51.330 --> 02:53.380
-Yeah.
-It's not an apartment.

02:53.380 --> 02:57.080
It's, um -- a warm,
separate environment

02:57.080 --> 02:58.960
where they can work out
their issues.

02:58.960 --> 03:00.880
It's a Ramada
with a mini-fridge.

03:00.880 --> 03:02.750
Guys, it's Mom and Dad.

03:02.750 --> 03:04.210
They're gonna be okay.

03:04.210 --> 03:06.040
They've been
through hard times.

03:06.040 --> 03:08.580
I mean, they survived AIDS
in the '80s,

03:08.580 --> 03:10.830
Suge Knight in the '90s,

03:10.830 --> 03:12.120
and they
potty-trained Jack.

03:12.120 --> 03:17.830
♪♪

03:17.830 --> 03:20.880
My brother and sisters were
clearly having a hard time,

03:20.880 --> 03:23.960
so I needed to be the glue
to hold us all together.

03:23.960 --> 03:26.120
I had to stop being Junior

03:26.120 --> 03:30.040
and start being
Andre Johnson Jr.

03:30.040 --> 03:33.170
Damn. That's just a longer way
of saying "Junior".

03:33.170 --> 03:36.790
I need to be...J.R.

03:36.790 --> 03:38.580
Oh, my God.

03:38.580 --> 03:40.670
How am I just now
getting that name?

03:40.670 --> 03:42.880
I could have been J.R.
through high school.

03:42.880 --> 03:44.620
Welp, better now than never.

03:44.620 --> 03:46.710
[ Door opens ]

03:46.710 --> 03:49.080
[ Sighs ]

03:49.080 --> 03:51.880
Oh, hey, big guy.

03:51.880 --> 03:54.710
Hey.
Let me help you
with your bag.

03:54.710 --> 03:58.040
We are all excited to start
your three days with us.
Mm.

03:58.040 --> 04:00.330
Couple of highlights
from me to catch you up on

04:00.330 --> 04:02.830
to make your parenting
experience enjoyable...

04:02.830 --> 04:04.540
-Mm-hmm.
-...and productive.

04:04.540 --> 04:06.750
Mm-hmm.
We are down to three
clean bowls, all right?

04:06.750 --> 04:08.920
Everyone is pretending
like the kitchen trash

04:08.920 --> 04:12.920
isn't overflowing,
and, oh, also my graduation

04:12.920 --> 04:14.380
is on one of your off days.

04:14.380 --> 04:15.620
I hope you can make it.

04:15.620 --> 04:17.500
-I'll try.
-Yeah, just relax.

04:17.500 --> 04:20.290
You know, the fridge
is over there, TV's there.

04:20.290 --> 04:22.540
Oh. [ Scoffs ] You know.

04:22.540 --> 04:26.040
Yeah, I do.
If you need anything,
Junior's --

04:26.040 --> 04:28.710
J.R.'s got you.
Yeah.

04:28.710 --> 04:31.710
Thank you, J.R.

04:31.710 --> 04:33.210
Don't mention it.

04:33.210 --> 04:35.670
Oh, it's the man
of the house

04:35.670 --> 04:37.380
on Tuesdays,
Thursdays, and Fridays.

04:37.380 --> 04:39.290
[ Groans ]
And alternating Saturdays

04:39.290 --> 04:40.880
and every other Sunday.

04:40.880 --> 04:43.670
Does no one understand
our temporary nest schedule?

04:43.670 --> 04:46.710
Boy, you need to stop pretending
that this isn't permanent.

04:46.710 --> 04:49.290
You realize that no one
comes back from space, right?

04:49.290 --> 04:51.620
That's why
they call it space.

04:51.620 --> 04:53.710
And I don't need to be the one
to tell you

04:53.710 --> 04:56.540
that divorce
will demolish your pockets.

04:56.540 --> 04:59.420
Okay.
I hope you like driving
a four-cylinder vehicle.

04:59.420 --> 05:01.580
-It's not coming to that.
-It better not.

05:01.580 --> 05:04.000
You're not built
for the single life, son.

05:04.000 --> 05:06.290
The only women available to you
will have problems.

05:06.290 --> 05:07.790
Not small ones.

05:07.790 --> 05:10.460
Talking about bad credit,
weird kids,

05:10.460 --> 05:12.380
all kinds
of medical conditions.
Okay.

05:12.380 --> 05:14.580
They'll wear braids
because they have to.

05:14.580 --> 05:16.080
[ Sniffs ]

05:16.080 --> 05:17.540
Pops, you're not helping.

05:17.540 --> 05:18.540
I'm not trying to.

05:18.540 --> 05:20.000
I see.

05:20.000 --> 05:21.790
Oh, hey, Dad.

05:21.790 --> 05:23.460
-Oh, hey.
-How you doing?

05:23.460 --> 05:24.960
I'm all right.
How are you guys?

05:24.960 --> 05:27.330
Good. Wait, you're not here
to kidnap us, right?

05:27.330 --> 05:28.500
What?

05:28.500 --> 05:30.750
[ Laughs ]
Just kidding.

05:30.750 --> 05:32.330
Okay. [ Laughs ]

05:32.330 --> 05:33.960
No, but seriously,
have you been patted down?

05:33.960 --> 05:35.330
-Hey.
-Just kidding.

05:35.330 --> 05:36.500
How about you
just give me a hug?

05:36.500 --> 05:38.290
Aww,
that's my baby girl.

05:38.290 --> 05:40.500
Mm-hmm. Mm-hmm.

05:40.500 --> 05:43.330
♪♪

05:43.330 --> 05:44.670
All right. Clear!

05:46.790 --> 05:48.580
Dad. Dad.

05:48.580 --> 05:49.580
Yeah?

05:49.580 --> 05:51.170
You [sniffs]
You smell something?

05:51.170 --> 05:53.080
-Jack, come on.
-No, no, no, no. No.

05:53.080 --> 05:55.920
This time it's not
my butt that's stinky.

05:55.920 --> 05:57.540
It's my leg.
What?

05:57.540 --> 05:59.960
[ GS Boyz' "Stanky Legg" plays ]
♪ Do the Stanky Legg ♪

05:59.960 --> 06:01.330
[ Laughs ]

06:01.330 --> 06:04.750
Hey, hey, turn with it!
Turn with it!

06:04.750 --> 06:07.460
Jack: I don't know
a lot about math or science,

06:07.460 --> 06:10.960
but I do know when I dance,
people get happy.

06:10.960 --> 06:14.120
♪ Do the Stanky Legg,
do the Stanky Legg ♪
[ Groans ]

06:14.120 --> 06:15.920
[ Laughing ] Oh, God.

06:15.920 --> 06:16.960
What are you doing?

06:16.960 --> 06:18.380
-"Stanky Legg".
-Okay.

06:18.380 --> 06:20.420
Yeah.
Do it with me. Come on.

06:20.420 --> 06:21.710
Okay.

06:21.710 --> 06:22.830
Hey.

06:22.830 --> 06:25.330
Are you going in?
Hey.

06:25.330 --> 06:27.120
I feel better when I dance,

06:27.120 --> 06:29.290
and so does everyone
that sees me.

06:29.290 --> 06:30.540
[ Laughter ]

06:30.540 --> 06:32.710
What the hell
is going on in here?

06:32.710 --> 06:35.790
[ Sniffs ] Ms. Biggs.

06:35.790 --> 06:37.420
You smell something?

06:37.420 --> 06:40.620
It's hotel soap.
I've fallen on hard times.

06:40.620 --> 06:42.040
No, no, Ms. Biggs.

06:42.040 --> 06:44.170
It's my Stanky Legg!

06:44.170 --> 06:47.040
[ Laughter ]
Okay, okay.
That's it.

06:47.040 --> 06:48.290
You're going
to the principal's office.

06:48.290 --> 06:50.250
Okay.

06:50.250 --> 06:53.080
I'll go
to the principal's office.

06:53.080 --> 06:56.620
But you're gonna have to drag me
there by my Stanky Legg.

06:56.620 --> 06:58.670
[ Laughter ]
Okay, come on now.

06:58.670 --> 07:01.420
♪♪

07:01.420 --> 07:02.830
Why are you looking at me
like that?

07:02.830 --> 07:04.500
Because it's your day.

07:04.500 --> 07:06.000
All right,
this is obviously not my fault.

07:06.000 --> 07:07.420
Well,
it's not mine, either.

07:07.420 --> 07:09.460
Hey, Mom,
can I ride with Dad?
No, sweetie.

07:09.460 --> 07:11.620
It's my day so you're
coming home with me, okay?

07:11.620 --> 07:13.080
All right.

07:18.790 --> 07:20.500
Dre: Bow and I had been trying
to keep it together

07:20.500 --> 07:23.460
for the kids, but the cracks
were clearly starting to show.

07:23.460 --> 07:25.080
-Can I have some ice cream?
-No.

07:25.080 --> 07:26.290
-Sure.
-I said "No."

07:26.290 --> 07:27.540
You just came home
from detention.

07:27.540 --> 07:30.000
Go to your room.
She's right. Go.

07:31.750 --> 07:33.710
What are you doing here?

07:33.710 --> 07:35.420
Well, I came to talk
to you about this.

07:35.420 --> 07:37.040
Yeah, we should
probably talk about this

07:37.040 --> 07:38.830
because Jack has been with you
for three days

07:38.830 --> 07:42.040
and now he is one warning away
from an in-school suspension

07:42.040 --> 07:44.250
and you are still
trying to be the fun dad.

07:44.250 --> 07:46.620
Okay, so [scoffs]
you're putting this on me.

07:46.620 --> 07:48.330
Well, I --
Well, I have to be
the fun dad

07:48.330 --> 07:50.120
because every time
I pick up the kids,

07:50.120 --> 07:52.790
they're so stressed
from you being the strict mom.

07:52.790 --> 07:54.290
Oh, ple-- [ Scoffs ]

07:54.290 --> 07:55.960
Dre, someone needs
to give them structure.

07:55.960 --> 07:57.290
Okay, and someone needs
to make sure

07:57.290 --> 07:58.540
they have joy
in their life.

07:58.540 --> 08:00.330
Oh, God.
Why do you hate joy?

08:00.330 --> 08:01.790
I don't hate joy, Dre.

08:01.790 --> 08:02.960
And you know what?
This is who you are.

08:02.960 --> 08:04.580
-Oh. [ Scoffs ]
-Is anybody making dinner?

08:04.580 --> 08:07.580
Oh, sweetheart.
We didn't know you were there.

08:07.580 --> 08:10.380
You know, we're just -- we're
just having a conversation.

08:10.380 --> 08:11.750
Yeah, we're --
we're not fighting.

08:11.750 --> 08:12.920
-No.
-We're just talking.

08:12.920 --> 08:14.670
-Yeah.
-I don't care.

08:14.670 --> 08:17.460
I believe discourse
is healthy and, sometimes,

08:17.460 --> 08:20.500
if it has to get physical,
it has to get physical.

08:20.500 --> 08:23.540
What? N-Nobody --
Nobody's getting physical.

08:23.540 --> 08:27.500
Diane: Unlike my weak siblings,
I was fine.

08:27.500 --> 08:29.580
If you think about it,
what in this world

08:29.580 --> 08:31.250
hasn't been made better
without conflict?

08:31.250 --> 08:33.380
There's no Magic without Bird.

08:33.380 --> 08:36.420
No Kyrie without LeBron.
No Whitney without Bobby.

08:36.420 --> 08:37.880
And then no Whitney
because of Bobby.

08:37.880 --> 08:40.380
[ Doorbell rings ]

08:41.880 --> 08:44.210
Oh, hey.
Sorry I'm late.

08:44.210 --> 08:45.580
It's okay.
I'm used to it.

08:45.580 --> 08:47.830
Okay. You know, I'm gonna go
upstairs and grab the watch.

08:47.830 --> 08:48.670
I have it right here.

08:50.580 --> 08:52.460
Okay,
this is my favorite watch.

08:52.460 --> 08:54.040
Why would we be giving
this to Junior

08:54.040 --> 08:55.330
for high-school
graduation?

08:55.330 --> 08:57.830
-Well, well, well.
-Sweetie.

08:57.830 --> 09:00.620
What is this bit of unscheduled
cross-parenting?

09:00.620 --> 09:04.000
Oh.
I mean, this deserves
a celebration.

09:04.000 --> 09:07.250
This occasion calls
for a screw-top Zinfandel.

09:07.250 --> 09:09.750
Wha--
I'm gonna go wait outside
of Trader Joe's

09:09.750 --> 09:11.960
for someone with boot-cut jeans
to buy it for me.

09:11.960 --> 09:13.290
All right?
-I -- Okay.

09:13.290 --> 09:15.330
Why do I feel like
you've done that before?

09:15.330 --> 09:17.210
Okay, look,
this is not about the watch.

09:17.210 --> 09:19.540
What are you t--
This is about you
not listening to me.

09:21.670 --> 09:23.460
Dre, it's very hard
to listen to somebody

09:23.460 --> 09:26.330
who is constantly
telling you you're wrong.

09:26.330 --> 09:28.540
Okay?

09:28.540 --> 09:30.330
Zoey:
So, I come home from college

09:30.330 --> 09:32.960
and Mom and Dad's marriage
is in shambles.

09:32.960 --> 09:34.170
So does that mean that when you

09:34.170 --> 09:36.420
fight with someone,
you love them?

09:36.420 --> 09:38.580
If so, then my
boyfriend, Luca, and I...
[ Cellphone vibrating ]

09:38.580 --> 09:41.080
...have been doing a lot
of loving lately.

09:41.080 --> 09:44.460
Hey, weirdo.
Why are you calling?

09:44.460 --> 09:47.460
Wait, what -- Why not?

09:50.040 --> 09:53.080
Well, can't you stop by
on your way there?

09:54.580 --> 09:57.380
Well, because I don't
want to Uber.

09:57.380 --> 09:58.880
Oh, so you don't know
why you deal with me?

09:58.880 --> 10:00.330
Well, then, don't.

10:00.330 --> 10:02.170
[ Sighs ]

10:03.380 --> 10:05.750
Okay, fine.

10:05.750 --> 10:07.420
Yeah, I'll see you in 10.

10:07.420 --> 10:09.790
I love you, too.

10:09.790 --> 10:11.580
[ Cellphone beeps ]

10:11.580 --> 10:13.790
[ Sighs ]

10:13.790 --> 10:15.380
[ Door opens ]

10:15.380 --> 10:17.250
[ Sighs ]
Oh, my God.

10:17.250 --> 10:18.580
[ Door closes ]

10:18.580 --> 10:21.290
♪♪

10:21.290 --> 10:22.290
I'm just really
worried about her.

10:22.290 --> 10:23.830
I've never seen
Zoey like this.

10:23.830 --> 10:26.500
Yeah.
I'm starting to see it, too.

10:26.500 --> 10:28.040
And it's not only her.

10:28.040 --> 10:29.710
You know,
Jack's acting out,

10:29.710 --> 10:32.290
Junior really wants
this to work for us,

10:32.290 --> 10:34.750
and Diane is even more
detached than normal.

10:34.750 --> 10:37.750
And that's saying a lot.

10:37.750 --> 10:40.500
The whole nesting thing was
supposed to protect the kids.

10:40.500 --> 10:43.000
Yeah.

10:43.000 --> 10:45.000
We're not doing a very good job
of that, are we?

10:45.000 --> 10:46.290
No.

10:46.290 --> 10:49.790
[ Gasps ]
There's my favorite couple.

10:49.790 --> 10:51.670
-[ Chuckles ] Hey, Linda.
-Hey.

10:51.670 --> 10:53.750
-Black love at its finest.
-Oh, yeah.

10:53.750 --> 10:56.080
My girlfriends and I were
talking about Cardi B and Offset

10:56.080 --> 10:57.670
and your black excellence
came up.

10:57.670 --> 10:58.750
Oh.

10:58.750 --> 11:00.250
How long have you two
been together?

11:00.250 --> 11:01.920
-Ooooh.
-Ooh, together a long time.

11:01.920 --> 11:04.710
We've been married...20?

11:04.710 --> 11:05.920
-Yeah.
-20.

11:05.920 --> 11:08.170
Look at God.

11:08.170 --> 11:11.250
I say to myself,
every Sunday when I tithe,

11:11.250 --> 11:13.420
my Prince Andre
is out there.
Oh.

11:13.420 --> 11:15.920
Definitely not at that church,
but he is somewhere.

11:15.920 --> 11:17.290
-Mm-hmm.
-Okay.

11:17.290 --> 11:19.750
Anyway, what brings
you two in today?

11:19.750 --> 11:23.000
We are here to get
a graduation gift for Junior.

11:23.000 --> 11:24.880
Yeah, I'm giving him
one of my old watches.

11:24.880 --> 11:27.420
Oh, man. Time flies, doesn't it?
[ Chuckles ]

11:27.420 --> 11:31.330
We just want, uh,
the watch to be engraved

11:31.330 --> 11:33.750
and for it to say
this right here.

11:33.750 --> 11:35.710
"We'll always be here for you.
Love, Mom and Dad."

11:35.710 --> 11:36.960
Mom and Dad.

11:36.960 --> 11:39.380
That's lovely.
Such black excellence.

11:39.380 --> 11:40.460
I'll have it ready for you
by Friday.

11:40.460 --> 11:41.500
-Thank you.
-Thank you so much.

11:41.500 --> 11:42.790
Oh, hey.
Don't forget the watch!

11:42.790 --> 11:45.000
-Oh, the watch.
-Oh. [ Laughs ]

11:45.000 --> 11:45.920
I love y'all.

11:45.920 --> 11:48.540
O-- Thank you.

11:48.540 --> 11:49.580
Wow.

11:49.580 --> 11:50.670
Yeah, wow.

11:50.670 --> 11:53.790
You know...

11:53.790 --> 11:56.040
Linda had a point.

11:56.040 --> 11:58.500
What?

11:58.500 --> 12:01.330
We do have
something special.

12:01.330 --> 12:02.500
That we do.

12:02.500 --> 12:03.880
[ Chuckles ]

12:03.880 --> 12:06.290
Ever since the beginning.

12:06.290 --> 12:08.790
We just got
to get back to us.

12:08.790 --> 12:10.330
Us.

12:13.170 --> 12:15.000
♪♪

12:15.000 --> 12:17.120
Dre:
Even though things were hard,

12:17.120 --> 12:20.710
Bow and I decided to try to
find our way back to each other

12:20.710 --> 12:23.000
for our kids, for ourselves,

12:23.000 --> 12:25.420
for Linda.

12:25.420 --> 12:27.540
I mean,
we're Dre and Bow Johnson.

12:27.540 --> 12:29.580
We've been together 20 years.

12:29.580 --> 12:32.250
We weren't going down
without a fight.

12:32.250 --> 12:34.420
Wow. The next time
you guys see me,

12:34.420 --> 12:36.040
I'll be a high-school
graduate.

12:36.040 --> 12:37.580
-[ Laughs ]
-I can't believe it.

12:37.580 --> 12:40.120
Oop, uh [chuckles]
not true.

12:40.120 --> 12:42.000
I forgot my cap.

12:42.000 --> 12:44.210
-Oh.
-Yeah. Thank you.

12:44.210 --> 12:45.420
And my gown.

12:45.420 --> 12:46.620
-Yeah.
-And your speech.

12:46.620 --> 12:48.250
Okay. All right.

12:48.250 --> 12:49.500
-Public school.
-I know.

12:49.500 --> 12:51.790
-[ Chuckles ]
-Is this seat taken?

12:51.790 --> 12:53.120
Oh, just sit, honey.

12:53.120 --> 12:54.830
You've reached the age
where people

12:54.830 --> 12:57.580
are uncomfortable sitting
while you're standing.

12:57.580 --> 13:00.790
Let's not pretend that you're
not five years older than me.

13:00.790 --> 13:01.620
Hi, sweetheart.

13:01.620 --> 13:03.120
Hi, Mom.

13:03.120 --> 13:05.250
Oh, there's Junior.

13:05.250 --> 13:07.710
Wait, that's --
No, that's Junior.

13:07.710 --> 13:10.460
He's so much harder to spot here
than he was at that prep school.

13:10.460 --> 13:12.880
No, there he is
right there.

13:12.880 --> 13:15.040
No, that's not him.
Don't matter.

13:15.040 --> 13:17.170
I'm not staying
for this whole thing, anyway.

13:17.170 --> 13:18.500
[ Chuckles ]

13:18.500 --> 13:19.710
[ The Police's
"Every Breath You Take" plays ]

13:19.710 --> 13:23.080
The Latin translation
of a valedictory

13:23.080 --> 13:26.540
is basically summed up
as a farewell to family.

13:26.540 --> 13:29.920
Let me tell you
what I've learned about family,

13:29.920 --> 13:33.710
that you can never really
say goodbye to family.

13:33.710 --> 13:37.460
♪ Every breath you take ♪
As we all go on to pursue
our individual dreams...

13:37.460 --> 13:41.330
♪ Every move you make ♪
...we'll always know we have
each other's backs...

13:41.330 --> 13:45.380
♪ Every bond you break,
every step you take ♪
...because with family
comes love and commitment.

13:45.380 --> 13:47.830
♪ I'll be watching you ♪
We all know what love is.

13:47.830 --> 13:50.080
Let's talk a little bit
about commitment.

13:50.080 --> 13:53.120
♪ Every single day ♪
It's the glue that binds...

13:53.120 --> 13:56.830
♪ Every word you say ♪
...anything important
in this world.

13:56.830 --> 14:00.580
♪ Every game you play,
every night you stay ♪
And I've learned commitment
from my parents.

14:00.580 --> 14:04.040
♪ I'll be watching you ♪
Commitment is what got
my dad out of Compton

14:04.040 --> 14:06.830
and into a house
in Sherman Oaks.

14:06.830 --> 14:08.880
♪ Oh, can't you see ♪
That's right.

14:08.880 --> 14:11.380
♪ You belong to me? ♪
Commitment
is why my mom graduated

14:11.380 --> 14:13.920
at the top
of her med-school class...

14:13.920 --> 14:16.830
♪ My poor heart aches ♪
...while nursing a newborn.

14:16.830 --> 14:18.080
Ruby: Mm-hmm.

14:18.080 --> 14:20.710
♪ With every step you take ♪

14:20.710 --> 14:22.710
Junior: And their commitment
to our family...

14:22.710 --> 14:25.580
♪ Every move you make ♪
...is why I'm standing here
today.

14:25.580 --> 14:28.620
♪ Every vow you break ♪
So, Graduating Class of 2018...

14:28.620 --> 14:31.750
♪ Every smile you fake ♪
...if we could develop
just a fraction...

14:31.750 --> 14:34.080
♪ Every claim you stake ♪
...of that fighting spirit...

14:34.080 --> 14:35.960
♪ I'll be watching you ♪
...there is nothing

14:35.960 --> 14:38.540
in the world that can stop us.

14:38.540 --> 14:40.120
That's right, baby.

14:40.120 --> 14:41.710
♪ Since you've gone,
I been lost without a trace ♪

14:41.710 --> 14:44.920
Junior: So, as I say goodbye,
remember...

14:44.920 --> 14:48.830
♪ I dream at night,
I can only see your face ♪
...it's not really goodbye...

14:48.830 --> 14:53.380
♪ I look around,
but it's you I can't replace ♪
...because you can never
really say goodbye to family.

14:53.380 --> 14:56.460
♪ I feel so cold,
and I long for your embrace ♪

14:56.460 --> 15:02.080
♪ I keep crying,
baby, baby, please ♪

15:02.080 --> 15:06.540
Class of 2018, we kept it lit.

15:06.540 --> 15:07.830
[ Cheers and applause ]
Go ahead, Junior.

15:07.830 --> 15:09.540
Ooh!
That's my grandbaby!

15:09.540 --> 15:10.960
♪ I'll be watching you ♪
Go ahead, Junior.

15:10.960 --> 15:14.960
♪ Every breath you take,
every move you make ♪

15:14.960 --> 15:17.080
♪ Every bond you break ♪

15:17.080 --> 15:19.120
♪ I'll be watching you ♪

15:19.120 --> 15:23.210
♪ Every single day,
every word you say ♪

15:23.210 --> 15:25.500
♪ Every game you play ♪
Thank you.

15:25.500 --> 15:27.290
♪ I'll be watching you ♪

15:32.960 --> 15:34.790
Junior, that was the best
valedictorian speech

15:34.790 --> 15:35.830
I have ever heard.

15:35.830 --> 15:37.290
-Mm-hmm.
-Absolutely.

15:37.290 --> 15:38.880
Except for the one
that I wrote...

15:38.880 --> 15:42.790
which I would have given had
the valedictorian fallen ill.

15:42.790 --> 15:44.880
That is a nice timepiece
you got there.

15:44.880 --> 15:45.920
Mm-hmm.
Thank you.

15:45.920 --> 15:48.250
-Watch your back.
-[ Laughs ]

15:48.250 --> 15:50.330
I got a car
and a trip to Europe,

15:50.330 --> 15:51.790
but your used watch
is nice, too.

15:51.790 --> 15:54.620
It is. I think this is
the nicest gift

15:54.620 --> 15:56.040
you guys
have ever gotten me.

15:56.040 --> 15:59.120
It definitely is,
and if it's ever between

15:59.120 --> 16:01.710
the watch and your life,
remember --

16:01.710 --> 16:03.380
you lived a great life.

16:03.380 --> 16:06.120
What? Dre.
[ Pops laughs ]
Come on, y'all.

16:06.120 --> 16:08.380
Let's clear this table so we can
get this Spades game going.

16:08.380 --> 16:11.120
Rainbow: Oh, yeah.
Ooh, I'm gonna whoop y'all's
asses in Spades.

16:11.120 --> 16:12.710
[ Laughs ]

16:12.710 --> 16:15.210
-He looks tired.
-Huh?

16:15.210 --> 16:16.380
I think I'm gonna
take him to bed.

16:16.380 --> 16:18.580
Yeah.
You look tired, too.

16:18.580 --> 16:19.920
Why don't you put
yourself to bed?

16:19.920 --> 16:22.290
-Stroke?
-Probably.

16:22.290 --> 16:25.080
Mwah! Good night.
Thanks, Mom.

16:25.080 --> 16:26.540
I'ma go get the cards,
guys.

16:26.540 --> 16:28.750
Okay.

16:28.750 --> 16:30.790
Hey. Bow?

16:30.790 --> 16:31.830
Yeah.

16:31.830 --> 16:35.080
You know, uh...

16:35.080 --> 16:36.670
Today's been
really nice.

16:36.670 --> 16:38.080
It has. I agree.

16:38.080 --> 16:40.120
Hey.

16:40.120 --> 16:41.330
I know it's not
your night...

16:41.330 --> 16:42.960
Mm-hmm.

16:42.960 --> 16:45.040
...but I was wondering
if you could stay over.

16:45.040 --> 16:47.290
I'll sleep on the couch.

16:47.290 --> 16:49.670
I just think it will
be a good thing for the kids

16:49.670 --> 16:51.170
to see us together
in the morning.

16:51.170 --> 16:52.830
Oh, Dre.

16:52.830 --> 16:54.330
I would if I could,

16:54.330 --> 16:57.250
but I have to be up at 5:00 a.m.
for call tomorrow.

16:57.250 --> 16:58.620
Call?

16:58.620 --> 16:59.960
Yeah,
I went back to work.

16:59.960 --> 17:01.750
When?

17:01.750 --> 17:04.330
A couple weeks ago.

17:04.330 --> 17:05.790
Why didn't you tell me?

17:05.790 --> 17:07.540
I don't know.

17:10.120 --> 17:11.580
I didn't know
I needed to tell you

17:11.580 --> 17:13.580
I wanted to make money
to support my kids.

17:13.580 --> 17:15.790
Okay, so -- so this is what
you've been doing?

17:15.790 --> 17:18.670
What?
Setting up
for a life without me?

17:18.670 --> 17:21.880
[ Scoffs ] This is why
I didn't tell you, Dre.

17:21.880 --> 17:23.250
'Cause I knew
you would overreact.

17:23.250 --> 17:24.620
This is what you do.

17:24.620 --> 17:26.670
No, no,
and this is what you do.
What?

17:26.670 --> 17:28.620
You change the rules
when you want

17:28.620 --> 17:30.420
and I have
to go along with it.

17:30.420 --> 17:32.250
You want to go to therapy?
We go.
No.

17:32.250 --> 17:33.500
You want to rotate
in and out of the house?

17:33.500 --> 17:34.960
We do.

17:34.960 --> 17:36.880
Have you made any other
life decisions without me?

17:36.880 --> 17:38.420
Hey, hey, come on now,
y'all.

17:41.170 --> 17:42.830
I'm not letting you
put this on me.
Oh.

17:42.830 --> 17:44.830
I'm doing everything I can
to fight for us.

17:44.830 --> 17:46.960
Well,
it doesn't feel like it.
What does that mean?

17:46.960 --> 17:49.290
It means
it doesn't feel like it.

17:49.290 --> 17:52.040
It means it feels
like this is broken.

17:52.040 --> 17:53.500
Then what are we doing?

17:55.170 --> 17:56.540
Because
this is exhausting.

17:56.540 --> 17:58.330
Oh, I see.

17:58.330 --> 18:01.330
I'm exhausted by you,
and you are exhausted by me.

18:01.330 --> 18:03.540
Yes, I am.

18:03.540 --> 18:05.750
What's going on?

18:05.750 --> 18:07.330
Nothing, sweet--

18:07.330 --> 18:08.290
Stop.

18:10.170 --> 18:12.500
Stop lying to me.

18:12.500 --> 18:16.670
Stop pretending
like everything is all right

18:16.670 --> 18:18.000
when it's not.

18:20.540 --> 18:24.080
God, I'm such an idiot.

18:24.080 --> 18:27.580
I believed you guys
were gonna be okay.

18:27.580 --> 18:30.080
But you were just faking it
this whole time.

18:30.080 --> 18:32.120
Has this all been
a lie?

18:32.120 --> 18:33.750
-Of course not.
-No.

18:33.750 --> 18:35.500
You know what?

18:35.500 --> 18:37.880
♪♪

18:37.880 --> 18:40.880
I'm done being lied to.

18:40.880 --> 18:42.880
Can everybody calm down?

18:42.880 --> 18:45.620
Zoey, what's happening?
Is this real?

18:45.620 --> 18:47.000
Is this really happening?

18:47.000 --> 18:48.330
Come on. Come --

18:48.330 --> 18:50.710
Jack: Diane.

18:50.710 --> 18:56.120
♪♪

19:00.540 --> 19:02.540
I've already
checked the hedges.

19:02.540 --> 19:04.040
I'm gonna look
over here.

19:04.040 --> 19:05.790
Okay.

19:08.830 --> 19:11.790
[ Sighs ]

19:11.790 --> 19:12.960
What are we doing?

19:12.960 --> 19:14.000
Trying to find
this watch.

19:14.000 --> 19:16.750
No, what are we doing?

19:16.750 --> 19:18.920
That was not us
back there.

19:18.920 --> 19:21.380
I don't know
who that was.

19:21.380 --> 19:22.670
And in front of everybody?

19:22.670 --> 19:23.500
I know.

19:25.580 --> 19:27.880
We can't keep doing this.

19:27.880 --> 19:28.920
It's not fair to the kids.

19:28.920 --> 19:30.080
It's not fair to us.

19:35.620 --> 19:37.710
[ Dog barking in distance ]

19:39.290 --> 19:42.210
I think we need
more than just space.

19:47.290 --> 19:49.290
I think so, too.

19:49.290 --> 19:58.620
♪♪

19:58.620 --> 20:01.960
♪♪

20:01.960 --> 20:04.580
[ Siren wailing in distance ]

20:04.580 --> 20:13.380
♪♪

20:13.380 --> 20:16.040
You okay?

20:16.040 --> 20:17.920
No.

20:17.920 --> 20:20.830
I didn't see this coming.

20:20.830 --> 20:24.170
I mean, they fought before,
but just not like this.

20:24.170 --> 20:26.080
I should've done more
to help them.

20:26.080 --> 20:27.880
I should've said more
in my speech.

20:27.880 --> 20:30.540
Uh-uh, don't do that.

20:30.540 --> 20:32.880
Martin Luther King could've
delivered that speech, boy.

20:32.880 --> 20:34.170
Same damn thing
would've happened.

20:34.170 --> 20:35.620
Pops is right.

20:35.620 --> 20:37.620
I don't want anyone in here
blaming themselves.

20:37.620 --> 20:39.830
When me and your grandma
split up,

20:39.830 --> 20:40.750
it wasn't anybody's fault.

20:40.750 --> 20:42.330
It was your fault.

20:42.330 --> 20:44.120
No, I mean,
that's how you felt then,

20:44.120 --> 20:45.120
but you've had time
to think about --

20:45.120 --> 20:46.960
Earl.
It was your fault.

20:46.960 --> 20:48.670
We saying the same thing.

20:48.670 --> 20:51.710
Truth is,
we split up 'cause we split up.

20:53.290 --> 20:54.710
Wasn't any
of our kids' fault.

20:54.710 --> 20:57.040
That's something I should've
told your daddy a long time ago.

20:57.040 --> 20:58.120
Mm-hmm.

20:58.120 --> 21:01.000
So, what now?

21:01.000 --> 21:03.380
Well,
nobody knows, baby.

21:03.380 --> 21:05.960
But whatever happens,

21:05.960 --> 21:10.500
we're never gonna stop
being family.

21:10.500 --> 21:19.710
♪♪

21:19.710 --> 21:23.460
♪♪
